sed by us to you, or accessed or provided by you, relating to the Beta Product, including your use thereof, the relationship contemplated herein, feedback, and the Product Terms (defined below), except to the extent made public by Facebook. You agree that you: (a) will not use any Confidential Information other than as necessary to use or test the Beta Product hereunder; (b) will maintain Confidential Information in strict confidence and will use the same degree of care to protect it as you use to protect your own confidential information, but in no circumstances less than reasonable care; and (c) will not disclose the Confidential Information to any person or entity other than those who need access to such Confidential Information to effect the intent of these Testing Terms and who are bound by written confidentiality obligations at least as protective as those set forth in this section; provided, however, that you will remain responsible for each such person\'s or entity\'s compliance with and breach of the confidentiality terms herein. You will not make any public announcements related to the Beta Product without our prior written approval, which we may grant or withhold in our sole discretion. This confidentiality provision supersedes any prior agreements between the parties solely with respect to Confidential Information hereunder.<br><br></li><li><u>Product Terms</u>. Facebook Product-specific terms and policies will also apply to your use of the Beta Product (the "Product Terms"). By continuing to access, test, or use the Beta Product, you agree to be bound by them. <br><br></li><li><u>Platform</u>. The following applies to your use of any Beta Product that is part of Facebook Platform (as defined in <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.facebook.com/terms">Facebook Platform Terms</a>). You agree that you: (a) will comply with <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.facebook.com/terms">Facebook Platform Terms</a>, <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.facebook.com/devpolicy/">Facebook Developer Policies</a> in connection with your use of the Beta Product.<br><br></li><li><u>Term</u>. With respect to each Beta Product, the term of these Testing Terms will begin on the Effective Date and, unless terminated earlier in accordance with the Applicable Terms, will continue until the earlier of (i) the date specified by us in our sole discretion (after which you will cease use of such Beta Product), (ii) the date when Facebook (in its sole discretion) makes such Beta Product generally publicly available (after which any permitted use is subject to Facebook Online Terms and not these Testing Terms), or (iii) the date when Facebook discontinue such Beta Product. These Testing Terms, as applied to each Beta Product, may be terminated by either party: (a) with cause immediately upon written notice to the other party; or (b) without cause upon seven (7) days\' prior written notice to the other party. Sections 2, 3, 4, 6 and 10 of these Testing Terms, and the provisions of Facebook Online Terms, will survive any termination or expiration of these Testing Terms.<br><br></li><li><u>Business terms.</u> You agree to test the Beta Product in conjunction with the "human agent" use case (i.e., providing customer service using human agents, including recommending products and services, and answering customer questions). You may use automation (i.e., means of responding to messages other than via human agents) to send "away" messages solely to communicate opening hours or hours of availability if the customer\'s message is received when the Client\'s business is closed (e.g., due to a public holiday or after business hours) or outside of the Client\'s live agent hours. You will otherwise only use human responders and will not use bots or other forms of automation (unless otherwise agreed in writing with FB (email sufficient)).Your App\'s integration with the Beta Product will<br>     include:<br>a. The ability to redirect or route messages to different queues and/or human agents;<br>b. The ability to mark a thread as processed/closed and hide it from the queue/main inbox, to ensure that the inbox is not filled with non-actionable threads.<br>You will use reasonable efforts to include inbox labelling including various levels of filtering/categorization (for example, the ability to label a message thread as "lead" or "follow-up") or build a similar labelling feature as part of your app\'s integration with the Beta Product.<br><br></li><li><u style="">Quality Requirement.<br></u>8.1 You will ensure your App\'s integration with the Beta Product always provides functionality to enable all messages with customers sent using the Beta Product on FB\'s Instagram and/or Messenger Platform to be escalated to human agents (even if you are permitted to use automation hereunder), and you will cause your Client\'s to provide human agents to receive, and respond to, such escalations. If you fail to do the foregoing, the number of Pages with which you may use the Beta Product may be limited or otherwise restricted.<br>You must respond to substantially all messages sent by users within twenty-four (24) hours of receipt during regular service hours of operation;<br>8.2 User opt in, authentication, and opt-out:<br>a. Don\'t contact people in Messenger unless you, or the party to whom you are operating as a service provider, have the necessary consent to do so. To the extent that you rely on user authentication to obtain consent to initiate message threads, place any user authentication methods in a clear and conspicuous location, with an easy-to-understand label or textual description which accurately and unambiguously describes the nature of and result of using such authentication.<br>b. Messenger opt-out: immediately respect all requests (either on Messenger or off) by people to block, discontinue, or otherwise opt out of your using Messenger to communicate with them.<br>8.3 Messenger Plugins:<br>a. Don\'t obscure, cover or hide elements of any Bitrix24 or Facebook plugins.<br>b. Ensure the Checkbox plugin is placed in close proximity to the button (ex: "purchase", "submit", "confirm") that a person must click on prior to you sending a MessengerCheckboxUserConfirmation event (i.e., don\'t send the event until after a person clicks on the button or takes an equivalent affirmative action (ex: submit form)). Include an easy-to-understand label or textual description that accurately and unambiguously describes the result of using the Checkbox plugin. For example: "Connect to us on Messenger." or "Receive receipts on Messenger."<br>8.4 Apps<br>Your App should not receive excessive negative feedback. Apps that receive excessive, negative feedback, may be feature limited, paused, rate-limited or removed from the platform. Be sure your App insights reflect a positive experience.<br>Maintain a Facebook Page that provides accurate customer support contact information, including your mailing address and one or more of the following: email address, web address, or telephone number.<br>8.5 Messages and Data:<br>8.5.1 Acceptable message types:<br>a. After people interact with your App: You may message people within 24 hours of a person\'s interaction with your Page or App (ex: messaging your App or interacting with a Messenger plugin on your website).<br>b. Message <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/messenger-platform/send-messages/message-tags">Tags</a>: Select message tags may be sent outside of the 24 hour period as described within our technical documentation. Monitor your block rate, to understand how people are responding to your messages. You may only use a message tag, template, quick reply or other structured message for its intended purpose as described within our <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.facebook.com/docs/messenger-platform/introduction">technical documentation</a>; don\'t use message tags, templates, quick replies, or other structured messages for any purpose other than its intended purpose.<br>8.5.2 Unacceptable message types<br>a. Pages or Apps may not facilitate person-to-person messaging, relays, or interactions that mask user identities from each other without giving individual users the ability to block other users within the messaging experience.<br>b. Sending spam as defined in Facebook Community Standards is not allowed. This includes behavior creating bots either manually or automatically, at very high frequencies; buying or selling feature privileges; facilitating or encouraging inauthentic behavior; failing to deliver promised experiences; directing users off of Facebook via deceptive or malicious URLs; and other substantially similar behavior designed to deceive or mislead users.<br>c. Do not use Message Tags to send promotional content or other advertising, marketing, or solicitations including but not limited to the promotion of goods or services; to upsell; communicate new product announcements; request donations; send daily deals, coupons, discounts or sale announcements; to send polls or user questionnaires.<br>8.5.3 News Messaging:<br>a. Only Pages that are registered and approved as News Publishers via the Facebook News Publisher Registration Process are eligible to use News Messaging. Other Pages including those that provide general updates from businesses, groups, interests, politicians or other entities with commercial, promotional, or political purposes are not eligible for News Messaging<br>b. News Messaging from approved News Publishers should be used to deliver timely newsworthy updates to users. News Messaging may not include promotional content or other advertising, marketing, or solicitations including but not limited to the promotion of goods or services including news subscriptions; to upsell; communicate new product announcements; request donations; send daily deals, coupons, discounts or sale announcements; to send polls or user questionnaires.<br>8.5.4 Data: Don\'t use any data obtained from us about the people you reach in Messenger, other than the content of message threads, for any purpose other than as reasonably necessary to support the message types you elect to use.<br>8.5.5 Healthcare: Don\'t use Messenger to facilitate direct conversations between people and healthcare providers or to send or collect any patient data obtained from healthcare providers.<br>8.5.6 Disclosures: Ensure that you provide all necessary disclosures to people using Messenger, such as any disclosures needed to indicate the sponsored or advertising nature of content you send.<br>8.5.7 Offers and Payments.<br>a. Don\'t share or ask people to share individual payment card, financial account numbers or other cardholder data within messages.<br>b. Don\'t include links to sites off Messenger where payment information is collected, without our prior permission.<br>c. If you have permission to offer or complete sales of goods or services within Messenger, adhere to the Facebook Commerce Product Merchant Agreement.<br>d. Don\'t use Messenger Platform to sell digital goods.<br><br></li><li><u style="">Instagram Platform<br></u>a. Be transparent about your identity and your App\'s identity.<br>b. Don\'t use the Instagram Platform for any App that constitutes, promotes or is used in connection with spyware, adware, or any other malicious programs or code.<br>c. Follow any instructions included in Facebook technical documentation.<br>d. Comply with any requirements or restrictions imposed on usage of Instagram user photos and videos ("User Content") by their respective owners. You are solely responsible for making use of Facebook User Content in compliance with owners\' requirements or restrictions.<br>e. Don\'t post unauthorized commercial communications or spam on Instagram.<br>f. Don\'t attempt to build an ad network on Instagram.g. Don\'t attempt to identify groups of individuals or create demographic clusters for the purpose of contacting or targeting Instagram members on or off Instagram.<br>h. You can administer a promotion on Instagram if you comply with Instagram\'s promotions policies and all applicable laws and regulations.<br>i. Don\'t use an unreasonable amount of bandwidth, or adversely impact the stability of Instagram.com servers or the behavior of other Apps using the Instagram Platform.<br><br></li><li><u>Miscellaneous</u>. You agree that your use of the Beta Product is subject to: as applicable, <a target="_blank" href="https://www.facebook.com/terms">Facebook Terms</a>, <a target="_blank" href="https://www.facebook.com/legal/commercial_terms">Facebook Commercial Terms</a>, <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.facebook.com/terms">Facebook Platform Terms</a>, <a target="_blank" href="https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fhelp.instagram.com%2F581066165581870%3Fhelpref%3Dpage_content&amp;h=AT0bzuzw7KlTE0pze9dqUqsNVetEGpGq5Pn1TCDNLC4e-ey6TuoLhcRpNMDnB8Cukr6Is1_hxiDOnNvzy10lBMEeoKNHtOUBjg6x6fnGtcwgUQjh_go8rv8-Q4tcqIlwE4NQCzs2w7FA_S5EpFZSeA">Instagram Terms</a>, <a target="_blank" href="https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whatsapp.com%2Flegal%2Fbusiness-terms%2F&amp;h=AT0aOjQAYnOlI2q2rVQ2Q-jY558kTcLNrdoGNCFH-LIuv4SzbsHhxzj07mNulb7kiDeQsRvU0HnUJRIZ_HD2eQprk0XUyFjUgH-BVhMUk6hNAw9OVrSg1LCwo-UzOQpDaH3Bp6pcyNCvSxekqO4ROw">WhatsApp Business Terms of Service</a>, <a target="_blank" href="https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whatsapp.com%2Flegal%2FFB-terms-whatsapp-business%2F&amp;h=AT1F2pdG_Y80O6ZUxyaovWt-tUCzpjqwpRsNVfFKnhEKJOrhye-1lfTij58RL0jqE-wcl_nfCh0DG0IQ_8cZge26Z4j-TEf-Ly_hy3kAUP61mGQceFQ1voqhOQ5sk8Fld505YFz-Fgn_x1T8Ud67_w">Facebook Terms for WhatsApp Business</a>, <a target="_blank" href="https://www.facebook.com/communitystandards/">Facebook Community Standards</a>, <a target="_blank" href="https://www.facebook.com/legal/commercial_terms">Facebook Commercial Terms</a> , <a target="_blank" href="https://help.instagram.com/477434105621119?helpref=page